# /design-to-plan — Convert Design Spec to Implementation Plan

Read a design spec and produce a sequenced, numbered implementation plan covering all layers.
Screen: **$ARGUMENTS**

## Configuration
- **Project root:** `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}`
- **Design specs:** `{{DESIGN_SPECS_PATH}}`
- **Contract registry:** `{{CONTRACT_REGISTRY_PATH}}`
- **Schema file:** `{{SCHEMA_FILE}}`
- **Backend source:** `{{BACKEND_SRC}}`
- **Frontend source:** `{{FRONTEND_SRC}}`
- **Component library:** `{{COMPONENT_LIBRARY_PATH}}`

## Steps

### Step 1 — Read Design Spec
Search `{{DESIGN_SPECS_PATH}}` for files matching "$ARGUMENTS".
Read the full design spec. Extract:
- **Data fields:** Every field name, type, and constraints
- **Components:** UI elements needed (tables, forms, cards, modals, etc.)
- **Status states:** Any status enums or workflow transitions
- **Role matrix:** Who can view, edit, create, delete
- **API endpoints:** Expected backend operations
- **UX notes:** Interactions, validations, transitions, notifications

If the spec is a stub or missing, report: "No actionable spec found. Write the spec first."

### Step 2 — Read Contract Registry
Search `{{CONTRACT_REGISTRY_PATH}}` for the screen entry.
Extract current status columns: DB, API, FE, INT, VER.
Note which layers are already marked as done.

### Step 3 — Read Database Schema
Read `{{SCHEMA_FILE}}` and identify:
- Which models from the spec already exist
- Which fields are missing from existing models
- Which relations need to be added
- Which enums need to be created

### Step 4 — Analyze Gaps
Compare the spec requirements against what exists. Categorize gaps:

**Database gaps:**
- Missing models
- Missing fields on existing models
- Missing relations
- Missing enums or enum values
- Missing indexes

**Backend gaps:**
- Missing controller endpoints
- Missing service methods
- Missing DTOs
- Missing validation rules
- Missing authorization checks

**Frontend gaps:**
- Missing page component
- Missing sub-components
- Missing hooks/data fetching
- Missing form validation
- Missing state handling (loading/error/empty/success)

### Step 5 — Generate Implementation Plan

```markdown
# Implementation Plan: $ARGUMENTS
Generated from design spec. Estimated effort: ~Xh

## Phase 1 — Prerequisites
[ ] 1.1 — [Any shared types, utilities, or dependencies needed first]
[ ] 1.2 — [Any third-party packages to install]

## Phase 2 — Database
[ ] 2.1 — Create/update model: [model name] with fields: [field list]
[ ] 2.2 — Add enum: [enum name] with values: [values]
[ ] 2.3 — Add relation: [model A] -> [model B]
[ ] 2.4 — Run migration and verify

## Phase 3 — Backend
[ ] 3.1 — Create DTOs: [create, update, query DTOs]
[ ] 3.2 — Implement service: [list methods with descriptions]
[ ] 3.3 — Implement controller: [list endpoints with HTTP methods]
[ ] 3.4 — Add authorization: [guards, decorators, role checks]
[ ] 3.5 — Register module
[ ] 3.6 — Write backend tests

## Phase 4 — Frontend
[ ] 4.1 — Create types: [type definitions needed]
[ ] 4.2 — Create hooks: [data fetching hooks]
[ ] 4.3 — Create sub-components: [table columns, form fields, cards]
[ ] 4.4 — Create page: [with all 4 states]
[ ] 4.5 — Add navigation entry
[ ] 4.6 — Add form validation

## Phase 5 — Integration
[ ] 5.1 — Wire frontend to real API endpoints
[ ] 5.2 — Test full CRUD flow
[ ] 5.3 — Test error handling (network errors, validation errors, 404s)
[ ] 5.4 — Test role-based access
[ ] 5.5 — Test edge cases from spec

## Phase 6 — Documentation
[ ] 6.1 — Update contract registry status columns
[ ] 6.2 — Update work log
[ ] 6.3 — Note any deviations from spec

## Dependencies
- [Step X depends on Step Y]
- [External blockers if any]

## Risks
- [Potential issues, unknowns, or scope creep areas]
```

### Step 6 — Estimate and Prioritize
For each task, provide a rough time estimate (15m, 30m, 1h, 2h).
Total up the estimate.
Highlight which tasks can be parallelized vs which are sequential.
Mark any tasks that are already done based on existing code.

## Output
Present the full implementation plan. Ask: "Start with Phase 1, or adjust the plan?"

## Notes
- Skip phases where everything is already built (e.g., if DB and API exist, start at Phase 4)
- Always include the integration phase — building layers in isolation leads to bugs
- Mark already-completed items with [x] instead of [ ]
- The plan should be specific enough that another developer could follow it
- If the spec has ambiguities, list them as questions at the end
